  <summary>&lt;p>A translucent variant of the material-based cursor&lt;br />&lt;br />based on bibata: &lt;a href="https://store.kde.org/p/1197198/">https://store.kde.org/p/1197198/&lt;/a>&lt;br />&lt;br />styles:&lt;br />Ghost: dark translucent variant&lt;br />Spirit: light translucent variant&lt;br />Tinted: orange translucent variant&lt;br />&lt;br />available in 22, 24, 28, 32, 40, 48, 56, 64, 72, 80, 88, and 96 pixel sizes&lt;br />&lt;br />get the latest build here: &lt;a href="https://github.com/Silicasandwhich/Bibata_Cursor_Translucent/releases">https://github.com/Silicasandwhich/Bibata_Cursor_Translucent/releases&lt;/a>&lt;br />&lt;br />Installation from github releases tab:&lt;br />Download and extract the archive. Then, run the script Installer_Bibata.sh. Run it as root to install for all users.&lt;/p></summary>
  <changelog></changelog>
